{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T02:48:54.671711558Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-7a875718","body":"finding_summary: `ProposeNewBead` findings are still routed into the restart amendment queue whenever the same final-review round also contains at least one `FixNow` item.\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:3312-3325\n- src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:7885-7906\nremediation_hint: Partition accepted amendments by `classification`, not just `mapped_to_bead_id`. Only `FixNow` should be enqueued for remediation; `PlannedElsewhere` should record mappings, and `ProposeNewBead` should stay deferred for downstream bead creation.","dedup_key":"bbcb6d57480b723ff4e6bf6fc7617b88c649359ccc79b5430f5f6d96a39bcaa3","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416021721","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T02:48:54.681005596Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-aceccf36","body":"finding_summary: The defensive duplicate check reclassifies against any same-title bead returned by `br list --all`, including closed beads (and the active bead itself), so it can suppress creation of a required follow-up bead by mapping to work that is no longer actionable.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2756-2764\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2871-2897\nremediation_hint: When rechecking for an existing match, ignore terminal/self matches or explicitly require an open/in-progress target before converting the finding to `planned-elsewhere`.","dedup_key":"08ecc0380c4fa0f2ce4f2e92964dd5ee123dad408bf3fbd2c8c5e406169ea17a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416021721","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
